Jaguar Plc &lt;JAGR.L> will spend about onebillion stg over the next six years on expanded production,automation and improved efficiency, Jaguar chairman Sir JohnEgan said.    He told reporters the company planned to raise productionto around 80,000 cars a year by 1992 from 47,000 this year,while productivity was expected to rise to 5.5 cars per workerin 1990 compared with four cars now.    Egan said the XJ6 model introduced last October was thefirst of a new saloon car family. Jaguar planned to bring out anew sports car in the early 1990s, probably called the "F." Reuter&#3;